Originally I hopped on this book's train for the thrill of being able to say I was reading it along with everyone else. But then something weird happened - I got hooked.The book's plot begins innocently enough (however, the few adult situations and strong language are anything but). The writing is interesting and very appealing to me. The narrators are writers and it is peppered with their inner thoughts. It doesn't read like a 3rd person talking at you from somewhere far away.Once I got to the Part II, there was a switch flipped and everything I thought I knew about how the story would go took a 180 twist. From then on all I wanted to do was read to find out what was going to happen next. The only thing I was disappointed about was that it ended.I will absolutely read more of Gillian Flynn's work. This particular book was the first GREAT read I've had since...well, a very long time!
From the very beginning Gone Girl keeps you on your toes and constantly has twists and turns that always makes you thirsty for more. If I had the time, i would have read this whole book in one sitting. We are led to believe one thing in book 1, then by book 2 we realize everything we know is a lie. By book 2 Nick is our protagonist and I was rooting for him and this is one of those books where you are squirming reading such horrific scenes because you learn to root for the characters, and are dying to hear that justice is served and everything works out in the end and the antagonist gets what they deserved. I hate to say I did not get the justice I would have liked to see at the end. But, I hate to say it fit for Nick's characterization.The writing was very well-written, very witty, which caught me laughing out loud at several times, and fuming at others. A great read that I will recommend to anyone.
I just finished Gone Girl by Gillian Flynn and found it to be an enjoyable read with plot twists that kept me turning the page late into the night. I had a hard time putting this book down and doing my chores, errands or even sleeping for a few nights! This is my first novel by this author and I will be buying her previous novels. I found the book to be well written, intense, and packed with the love, hate and upheaval that can happen between 2 people when they spend their lives together. Was there cruelty? Was there spite? Was there laughter? Were there tears? Was it human? Was it inhuman? Yes! And it was very frightening, the lengths they went to in order to hurt one another. But finally, a book I could read without predicting every twist and turn and feeling sure of the ending. Thank you for that! As for the ending of this story (no spoiler here), many people were disappointed. I found it perfect.
This is one of the few books to ever genuinely surprise me. I've read many horror, mystery, thriller books, and while the author had ""twists"" in it, nothing comes close to this book. I laughed out loud at many parts, but more importantly to me, I gasped out loud. I don't want to give anything away, but I'm disturbed by the fact that I actually liked Amy and Nick together, and after I finished the book, my brain was still processing what I had just read, and all I could do was laugh. The author does a great job of giving both sides (Amy and Nick 's) without leaning in favor of one character over the other. I would recommend this book to anyone in a healthy marriage, I would advise caution to everyone else...just kidding. Well, sort of. (Haha). If you like mystery and/or thrillers, this is a great read. Nothing gory, just mentally disturbing. Well written. Enjoyable despite its controversial topics.
I read so many books and see so many TV shows and movies, that I can almost always figure out ""who done it"" in the first five minutes or the first 50 pages. That was not true with Gone Girl. It is the best written and best plotted book Ive read in a long time. Gillian Flynn has an amazing ability to get inside her characters minds and describe in great descriptive detail what they are thinking and feeling. I told a friend ""I have never written a book, but if I had, I would want it to be as good as this one"". I have given Kindle editions and hard cover copies to five of my friends. Some were male, some were female and their ages varied greatly. All of them without exception raved about Gone Girl. Honestly, do yourself a favor and buy this book. I think you will soon be buying more copies as gifts. I am deliberately not saying anything about the plot because to do so would deter from your enjoyment.
