I read this book because I had seen it listed on the NY Times Bestsellers list for weeks on end--I figured it had to be worth it. It was.Each chapter changes back and forth from Nick's POV to Amy's diary entries (dating back years, and eventually becoming something else entirely).Amy goes missing on her and hubby's (Nick) 5th (I think) anniversary...you get the feeling that something is off, but cannot put your finger on it. When you get to Part 2, your mind will be blown. As for the ending...I have read a few reviews that it was underwhelming, but I found it to be right in line with the characters personalities and I think most people can draw their own conclusions.I highly recommend this book! So good, I had it done in a weekend.
