I didn't know what I was getting myself into when I started reading this book. A friend recommended it, and I didn't believe that it was going to be nearly as intricate or complicated to begin with.The characters are complex and well written. The story is hard to put down. It leaves you feeling sympathetic for both of the main characters at different times. It is also a little baffling to think of the forethought needed to make it all work. Overall, I truly enjoyed the novel and all of the twists and turns. The only disappointment is the way the book ended. That is not to say that it was bad, by any means, and it totally fits the story to a T. However, I am always satisfied when justice is served as closure, and that does not ring true for this story.
Gone Girl"" by Gillian Flynn is a sinister and wickedly clever novel that captures your attention from the start and keeps you hanging on until the end. Seeing both perspectives of husband and wife is a brilliant way to tell the story, throughout most of the story the reader is left utterly confused about both main characters personalities and ""who they really are."" I often asked myself, ""Should I trust this character?"" There are many twists and turns in this novel that jump out at you, right as you think you may have some information pieced together you get hit with a plot twist. This is definitely a recommended read. Be warned, once you pick this book up and dive into the world of ""Gone Girl"" you will not be able to leave.
Gone Girl"" was delivered to me in great condition - basically new! Not a page dogeared, not a stain nor smudge. The seller upheld every portion of their delivery promise and because of that, it made reading the novel extremely enjoyable.The plot twists, the amazing description and development of characters made this book one of the better I've read in the last three years. Amy Dunne is an amazing character achievement in literature and I am confident she will go down as such in the future. Cunning, manipulative, and sexy - what's not to love?I would absolutely purchase more merchandise from this seller and would recommend ""Gone Girl"" for anyone looking to caught all-too-caught-up in a stylish, mysterious thriller.
