It took a long time to read this book, which is not my style. And this is mainly because it was just too unbearably awful, but also chillingly plausible. When the main characters of any novel are irredeemably unlikeable, but brilliantly written and somehow utterly, creepily familiar to you- it's hard to go on. Because you recognize that particular brand of narcissistic evil, from the hidden, gossamer-webbed corners of your own Other. Go ahead, read this one and be aghast. You know it's a little piece of you in those pages.
