I read and edit for a living, so in order for me to want to read outside of my job, a book really needs to grab me or I'll lose interest quickly. This book had me on the edge of my seat from the very beginning. The pace is incredible quick, and the plot line keeps you guessing about what really happened and who is telling the truth. The language can be a bit raw, but it is brilliantly written and completely captivating for mystery/suspense lovers. Highly recommended.
