I can't recall ever reading a book which whipped my emotional sympathies for the characters back and forth so mercilessly or so perfectly. Flynn writes with an exceptional voice, and in turn brings a life to her characters that make you feel like you've met them. The novel itself even seems to shift like a chamelon between mystery to suspense to thriller with even a bit of dark comedy laced in. Brilliant.
Gone Girl was a book I had a hard time putting down. It was a fascinating study of who people appear to be and who they really are. The way you want others to see you is often the way you want to be yourself - even if your facade is a lie. If you showed the one you love your true self - would they still love you?A wonderful mystery of twists and turns and an interesting look inside a marriage.
Gillian Flynn's GONE GIRL:A NOVEL is one of those books that twists and turns and then snakes back again until the final scene which ends in the only possible way it could. The writing is excellent, and as one who has studied marriages and families, Flynn does a superb job of depicting a disturbing and disturbed relationship. I would recommend it for anyone who wants to be involved as well as entertained.
