I don't often write reviews on Amazon, i don't have time for that, and I don't care too much to do it. However, I made an exception for Gone Girl. This book is about a man and a women going through a rough patch in their marriage, except it's a lot more twisted then that and like many other reviews I can't write more about what goes on because it will ruin the whole plot. I can say that I haven't enjoyed a book  as thoroughly as I enjoyed Gone Girl. By the end of part one I was confused at what to think anymore, by the end of part two I was like ""crap, this girl is crazy"" and by the end of part three I had a huge goofy grin on my face and all i could think about was ""what just happened?"".Gillian Flynn is a writer, she knows how to write, string you along, and  she has a talent of not categorizing things in black or white. I loved the book because of the way she ended it. It wasn't the typical ending and that would make some people mad, but I don't read books because I want to have things end predictably, I read books because it's an escape from the mundane, to feel giddy, happy, suspenseful, and distracted from the tube, and she did all that in Gone Girl, I'm still smiling because of the ridiculousness of this book!
