The novel, Gone Girl, is a fascinating novel that was written by Gillian Flynn and published in the year 2012. The novel opens up with a story where a young couple Nick and Amy are getting into their fifth wedding anniversary and Amy disappears and whether Nick Dunne is able to kill his wife Amy.  As Jeff Giles said about the book “there’s not a lot I can tell you about gone girl without raining its dark surprises”. Also, he believes “no matter how smart you think you are, it's going to bite you”. I agree with jeff Giles, because after reading this book, I can say that one of the best thing about the novel, that it’s keeps the reader guessing. Also, what I really like about the book is that it is a story that it is told in different ways, the husband and the wife which make it more interesting. Overall this book is very good book not just because it is a great crime story, and build up, but at the same time it is a story that started as many marriages, and it touch many themes and things that can happen to anyone in real life, Also the book shows the effects of many things such as Money, and parents on marriage.
Gone Girl blew up in 2012 after its release. As it was, I was skeptical to read it. A book's popularity is very polarizing for me. I either must get my hands on it immediately or have absolutely no desire to read it. In the beginning, it was the latter for me. Gone Girl just didn't appeal to me. Then, as has happened to me numerous times before, I saw the movie trailer. The idea of a movie has a way of intriguing me and making me pick up books I otherwise wouldn't have even bothered with (especially if said movie has an interesting trailer). And so, I finally decided to read Gone Girl.This book was so much better than I thought it would be. Yes, it was the Goodreads Choice Winner of 2012 (Mystery & Thriller), but I read so many negative reviews. I can't count how many times I saw people complain about the ending. So, even though it is an award winning book, I went into it not expecting to be wowed since so many other people were disappointed. Nope! I loved it. It's twisty and full of turns. It's dark and absolutely crazy. It was everything that I love in a mystery/thriller.And I, for one, liked the ending.
