Gillian Flynn's GONE GIRL is an amazing read!  The two main characters, Nick and Amy, alternate POV chapters, which puts the reader deep inside each of their heads as the story unfolds.Nick and Amy wake up and start their 5th anniversary over crepes, and that's pretty much when their 'normal' life ends.  Nick gets a call from a concerned neighbor that afternoon, then rushes home to find signs of a struggle and his wife missing.This story is written with so many plot twists and zingers, it was hard to put the book down. The characters, like real people, are flawed, a few more so than others. As the investigation gets underway, and as Nick follows his wife's notes for their anniversary 'treasure hunt', their less than perfect marriage is revealed, complete with infidelities and financial problems.So....what happened to Amy? Why? Who is responsible???  You HAVE GOT TO READ THIS BOOK to find out! The author is even more amazing than AMAZING AMY.
