Fascinating, thrilling--a great book!  I could not stop reading.  Amy will keep you on the edge of your seat--and maybe awake at night.
This complicated mystery was super and kept me reading until the end.  The chapters are very short and written from the point of view of the two major characters, with chapter titles of simply ""Nick"" or ""Amy"".  Some of the book is presented in diary form.  The story is very complex.  Hard to believe that anyone would have the skill and persistence to carry out a plot to ruin a spouse in such a wide variety of strange ways.  I don't have time to read at length, so I kept it handy and read a few chapters quickly when I got a short window of time.  The only thing that disappointed me is the ending, but I believe that it is designed like a season's closing of a soap opera or sitcom, creating a jumping-off point if a sequel is in the future. This novel was recommended by a friend for a book club selection, and it certainly did not disappoint.  It generated positive responses from every member.  I would definitely read other novels by Gillian Flynn.
Gone Girl is the story of a missing woman, and the (suspicious) husband who doesn’t seem to be overly concerned … or is it?  Just as I believed I had unraveled the mystery and arrived at a conclusion, the author shifted the point of view midway through the book, completely changing my perception of the main characters and my previous assumptions.  The novel picked up speed, hurtling toward an ending that is abupt, and at first, I was disappointed and felt as if the author had abandoned the story.  However, when I realized that Flynn’s characters weren’t going to be changed for the better and that my sense of justice might not prevail, I could appreciate the author’s intent—to tell a story that kept me guessing, turning pages furiously, all the while suppressing the desire to peek at the ending.  Flynn writes with an amazing attention to detail, providing an endlessly twisting plot and characters that are so flawed the reader cannot help but react to them.
This book is cleverly written. Its rare that a book keeps my interest all the way, Gone Girl did!!  Definitely a page-turner!
Everyone should read this book.  It MAY be about a situation that affects one particular guy (in the book) but its really about how PEOPLE actually can live this way IN REAL LIFE.  I have a sister who does this kind of stuff ALL THE TIME and NO ONE believes me when I tell them!  She can plan something YEARS in advance and WHO is ever going to know?  First, NO ONE CARES but the persons who are affected and THEY DON'T EVEN KNOW they've been manipulated and/or lied to.  So, read this book and be aware of those around you who do this sort of thing...I don't know that my sister is capable of doing some of the things the ""gone girl"" did (like murder, though she did stab me with a pencil when we were very young - I still carry the point of the pencil in my hand where I put my hand up to ward off the strike), but some of the things my sister did (and continues to do as we speak) are sinister and plain evil.  Still waiting for KARMA to even things out...
