This book is a real page turner, it is dark and mind boggling. The author really captivated the true essence of what we call a “toxic relationship” like the relationship of amy and nick. Love is really a powerful feeling that can drive us through great lengths, it can make us do crazy, stupid and even dangerous stunts just to make a relationship work. This book has all the elements that can make us think who the bad guy really is in the story. Great story plot and the way the author portray the characters. It is not a one sided book wherein there’s only one narrator which can be a real drag at times. When I finished this book it left me with my mouth open and i said “what the heck was that” lol. If you’re into dark, challenging, mysterious reads, you will like this book. Cant wait to watch this on the big screen on October 3. This a definitely must read, I had fun reading this book, two thumbs up for me.
This is a wonderfully twisted novel and Gillian Flynn deserves every accolade she has received for it.  So much has been written and reviewed about it that nothing more need be said, so I will list my only two ""complaints"" about the book.1.  It is a bit over-written.  It felt at times that Flynn as trying to impress the reader with her voluminous knowledge of American culture.  There are so many references to current pop culture icons, as well as occasional sly references to things only New York writers know or care about, that it became distracting.2.  I am astonished that everyone who talks about the book -- even Flynn herself -- frames Nick and Amy as ""the couple from Hell"" or the relationship as just mindbogglingly ""dysfunctional"" and that I have yet to hear one person peg Amy for what she truly is (or at least comes off as on the page):  a sociopath.
