Gillian Flynn’s “Gone Girl” is thrilling, eerie, and mesmerizing!  Nick and Amy once had a great relationship, but recently they have been stuck in rut.  As with many couples they experience the trials and tribulations of being married including financial problems and failed attempts of conception.  This unfortunate lull has turned chaotic as Amy disappears leaving clues in her wake.  The reader sets out on a journey with Nick as the clues are traced, diary entries read, and the twists curve around every corner.  Flynn leaves her readers constantly guessing as to who killed Amy, where she went, and will she return?Without giving too much away, I will note that this book is edgy and intriguing!  It is a must read!  I look forward to seeing the differences and similar on the big screen this October!**I’d also recommend reading Flynn’s “Sharp Objects.”
