Based on my previous purchases, this book continued to pop up as something I should read via a number of emails from Amazon. I put it off for a few months until I ran out of my favorites and decided to give it a try. I normally don't read female authors and I need to reevaluate why that is. This book is ""amazing"" ! It starts off very descriptive and dreamy and easy to read but you get a sense that things could turn strange at any moment. Well, it sure does. This book continues to pick up steam with each page and ended up requiring me to set aside most of a Sunday to finish it as I could not put it down. This book is quite frightening to read and really makes you think. The ending was a bit unexpected and I am not sure how I feel about it but, I thoroughly enjoyed it and will probably now add Gillian Flynn to my list of authors to read.
So often we tell each other ""That was a really good book."" But how does one define ""good""? It could mean almost anything. My definition is that it keeps me guessing, wanting more, and putting off important tasks so I can turn the next page. If the book is ""good,"" I want to get back to it, thank you. I have to confess it's been a long time since I read a book that I wanted to get back to this much. Ms. Flynn certainly knows how to write. No wasted words. She took me on an emotional ride, and I let her manipulate my feelings the whole time. That was the fun of it. Plus, the book is really thought-provoking. What is really going on in people's heads? And the ending that so many have criticized? Pure perfection. Loved it. Do I want more of Nick and Amy? Oh, yes. More please.
I had the unfortunate luck to not read this book before I saw the movie. So let me be the first to tell you to not do as I did: Don't wait for the library kindle edition to be available, buy the book.Books are (usually) better than movies, but it is especially delightful when the book is better than the movie and the movie is excellent.Flynn wrote a chilling realistic novel that will suck you in. The realness of the characters struck chords with me as I read, and certain lines left me with chills. Particularly, repetition of marriage questions, ""What are you thinking? How are you feeling? What have we done to each other? What will we do?""A truly delightful antagonist and a protagonist you aren't sure you can really trust: Go read this novel. Then go see the movie.You can thank me later.
