SPOILER: For those of you who said the ending was unsatisfying, I know what you would've wanted to happen. But Gillian ended it BEAUTIFULLY, I think; because that's how life is. There aren't always happy endings where justice is served and the bad guy is defeated. Sometimes the bad guy wins or we're left with the illusion that the bad guy got what he or she wants and that's OK. That's life. Plus if Amy didn't end up getting most of what she wanted (definitely not everything she wanted because she ends the book by saying that she really wished Nick wouldn't have said what he said), then all that time spent crafting her into a brilliantly ""Psycho Birch"" would have been wasted. She was an evil genius. You hate her but you can't help be amazed by her ever churning brain power. Loved the book...left me in awe.
The best book I've read in the past couple of years.A ""whodunit?"", or rather, ""did he do it?"" with constant twists and angles and insightful descriptions.Love the writing style. The characters were constantly developing and changing. Each half of this troubled couple constantly juxtaposed against the other. Just fascinating.Because it didn't garner favorable reviews from everyone, even being so wildly successful, I was prepared for the ending perhaps not being what I, and I expect all those disgruntled others, wished it would be.But the final two sentences quickly ended the impending doom of the novel not being tidied up so neatly. Just had to laugh out loud after reading the end. Gillian Flynn redeems that impending doom with one last bite of humor. Hurrah!
