I really enjoyed this book, I could not see where the story was going and I liked that, I like being surprised!
When I first started reading Gone Girl, I will admit I was wondering what all the hype was about. As I got further along I was really interested in the characters and I needed to know what was going on and how the story was going to play out. THEN I got to part two “Boy meets Girl” and my mind was BLOWN. I could not believe the plot twists and I couldn’t put the book down. Flynn really did a good job at not hinting the plot twists to the reader all the while making you feel totally involved in the unraveling of the story. A lot of people are upset about the ending, but I think that it just showed the severity of how dysfunctional every bit of the relationship between Amy and Nick was. I loved this book and I would recommend it to any one who wants to get wrapped up in a juicy, messy, thriller!!
I picked this book up at a grocery store as an after thought because I heard it was going to be a movie.  I initially thought, based off the premise, that it was a murder mystery story.  It turns out that it was a great psychological thriller on par with Fight Club, Alfred Hitchcock's Psycho and American Psycho.  The two main characters are so well developed that you care what happens to them even though they are terrible people.  The twist in the middle in which it turns out that Amy is a complete sociopath was ingenious.  My only gripe is that the ending was completely unsatisfying.  I don't want to spoil anything, but I felt there should have been a better resolution to the story.  That wasn't enough for me to take away a star.  I highly recommend this book and I can't wait for the movie.
