You will experience many of your emotions about the characters' actions in a visceral way.  As a result, you are going to be really ticked off, surprised, no SHOCKED, by the sharp turns - courtesy of Flynn - in the story. Just be prepared for a roller coaster ride!!  Women: maybe don't read it at the end of your cycle (I am a woman so please don't be offended), if you tend to be a tad more sensitive at that time.  Men: well I believe you guys have your own version of a ""cycle"" (maybe it's not controlled by a 21 day pack - Lol), so the same advice goes to you.  Oh and be prepared to have outbursts, similar to ones you recall your mother having while watching soap operas/telénovela, or your dad while watching football/fútbol. *Or vice versa on the mom/dad roles.  :)
