There are so many layers to Gillian Flynn's Best- Seller-Turned- Major- Box- Office- Breaker.It engages you from the very start, and like the best crime stories- it gives you everything you need to know without actually giving it to you. You might think you see where it's going, but even if you have an inkling- you have no idea what you're in for: the sheer depth of the characters' psyches hits you right in the guts, throughout all the novel. It's an amazing read, and- more astoundingly, especially for a mystery novel- it's one you can read, re-read, analyse, and read again, simply being astounded once more with every  read.
