An extremely well-crafted psychological thriller; it held my interest from the first word to the last. And there are a lot of words in between. I recall hearing that it took Flynn four years to write this book. Given the very complex plot, it's easy to believe. But glad she took the time so that there would be no loose ends. The only thing that felt weak was the ending. It seemed to pop up suddenly while I was still deep inside the complexities of the characters' behaviors. Flynn's ability to create tension as a result of those behaviors is a testament to her ability as a writer. I think I'll have to look for more of her work.
