I saw the movie first and had no idea what I was getting myself into.  It left me wondering: how much of the diary flashbacks were real, and how much was imagined for the sake of Amy's clever plotting? The book provides much deeper insight into both main characters and better explains the diary entries, keying in on themes that question the nature of human authenticity in a world saturated with typecast characters that provide the script for all our interactions.  Through breaking our expectations of what one one can do to spurn--and ultimately return to--one's partner, Flynn writes her own script and beckons us follow.
