A couple of young lovers from the big city head to a small town to find paradise. Or do they? Upon arrival in the backwaters of Missouri two people who knew each other so well discover they may not have guessed the deep inner secrets each holds. And one of them suddenly is gone. From here winds a tale that keeps the reader always finding the ""right"" clue, only to lose it again. I have to say I was ready for a chic book, but Ms. Flynn's tale is a great read for the guys looking for that mystery that is not based on a sad sports hero. I confess as well, I never guessed the end. A can't put down read.
