A wild ride inside the psychotic minds of two deeply flawed individuals. Flynn has written this book in a unique style. She keeps the reader fully engaged. I couldn't put it down. Flynn's subtle introduction, development and revelation of the psychosis of the main characters is extraordinary. I would love to know where she acquired her knowledge and insight for the detailed character development. The way she wove the intricate plot into the thought processes of the antagonist was masterful. I don't think I have read anything quite like it. Highly recommended if you like dark thrillers.
