A winner.  While the title leads you to believe this is ""chic lit,"" it isn't at all.  It's about an alleged crime, a complex relationship, not to mention delusions and deceit.  As the layers of the onion peel away and the reader is given a new and sometimes utterly unexpected piece of information, you find yourself ping-ponging between whose side you're on when ten minutes earlier, you would have staked your life on who was the victim and who was the perpetrator.  While the main characters are equally unsympathetic, they are meticulously drawn and magnetically interesting.
