Amy's parents, the Elliott's, are authors and throughout Amy's childhood wrote a series of books about ""Amazing Amy"".  I believe this had a strong influence on how Amy developed & how she learned to play act her way through life. Amy is actually the real author, writing her life using her ability to anticipate the ending (strong 20/20 foresight) and she develops her life story line accordingly. Amy acts out roles and those in contact with her unwittingly play their parts. Nick figures out how to turn the tables but Amy is just so good at it...... I thoroughly enjoyed this book.
