I've never read anything quite like Gone Girl by Gillian Flynn.  It's a psychological thriller from start to finish.  The mind games thatthese characters play are just amazing.  I was totally drawn into the storyline, and began to feel a little claustrophobic as the plotthickened throughout the book.  Suspenseful and, yes, a little terrifying, at times.  I would recommend this to anyone who likes agood psychological study of two characters who are totally wrong for each other and yet try to live together as husband and wife.
