This is a terrific book. The writing is first rate and the plot is intricate and fascinating. Without giving the story away, the complexities of two people in a marriage falling out of love and into resentment and anguish is handled with such delicious skill that the reader, even polished mystery readers who know the end of the book after reading the first page, are carried along because of terrific plotting and writing. Gone Girl could be a primer for a class on marital dysfunction and therapy. By all means, read it before you see the film.
