In one word ""Brilliant"". I was looking for a unputdownable book and read about it on the Amazon list. What a find. Beautifully constructed plot and characters. Love to hate them and in the end don't know who to sympathise with! Keeps you guessing (though I guessed a bit:)) Lyrical at times especially its take on soulmates and single child. And what a take on marriage! A great book for any thriller buff. Actually a must try for anyone. Read it in a day flat. That good. Though the end could have been shorter. Dragged a bit.
This story had me hooked from the beginning. The characters were so well crafted: I knew them, I saw them, they lived and breathed. Vivid, vivid! The story line itself at a 50,000 foot view is not original: wife disappears and the husband is the prime suspect. What is spectacularly original is the way the author reveals the story, with a his and hers point of view, allowing the reader to be pulled in, and the carpet to be pulled out from under us. We become as agitated, infuriated and helpless as the story's protagonist.
This book is brilliant, but what a roller coaster!  You're never sure what the heck is going to happen next, never sure who you should root for, if anyone.  The first half is great, but once it hits about the halfway point, I started wanting to do nothing but read constantly.  Stay up too late, not go to work, whatever, just give me some more of that yummy book.  Thinking maybe I should switch to something light and fluffy for my next read, give my psyche a rest, but am very interested in what else Ms. Flynn has written.
