Gillian Flynn always delights me with her raw, honest emotions. Living in the corporate world, I know people show one face to the public, and live in a whole other world internally. Gillian captured, beautifully, the nature of most human's crazy balance of our inside voices versus the voice we show the world. Life is not perfect. We make choices and live with them. Too many books try to rewrite the world to make everything always turn out perfectly. This book says, ""Yep, sometimes life sucks-deal with it."" I loved it.
