I read this book based on recommendations from friends. I could not put it down once I started. It is such an in depth look at a disfunctional marriage, the compromises and the consequences of Amy and Nick's marriage. I went back and forth from loving, hating and understanding these characters then feeling bad and justified when each feeling was validated. Gillian Flynn has really gotten underneath the skins of this couple and once you have finished reading it, you will never look at your spouse in the same way!
