There are twists and turns. And in the end you will find yourself twisted , like a vine. Rooting first for one. Then the other. And then for them both. Loving one. Hating the other. Waxing and waning like the moon. I love it when love and hate; awe and loathing; and all the other emotions that share a decidedly fine line between blur into a Monet of impressions that you ultimately feel simultaneously. By the time you figure out the twist, you are too intertwined with the characters to put the book down. Enjoy!
