I was really surprised by this book. At first I thought it was going to be the whole wrongfully accused husband thing, but then it turned into something completely different. It was a good read that held my interest and had unexpected turns. It is definitely not a happy book but I thought some of the dark truths about marriage were fairly accurate (although I don't think most of us would go as far as they do in the book). Overall I would recommend it and I am curious to see how the movie will be.
I had a love/hate relationship with this book...much like the main characters had with one another! At times I felt sympathy for the characters, at other times I thought they got what they deserved.  Sometimes I wanted to throw the book across the room, yet I kept picking it up to see what happened next. I gave the book 5 stars because for once I had NO idea how it would turn out...usually you can pretty well predict who will end up with whom, and who the guilty party is, etc.  Not with this one!
