This book grabs you a little slowly, I thought.  But once it has your attention, you can't stop until you are done.  I particularly loved the last chapter.  The writer has grasped the narcissistic personality and carried it to a whole new level.  I personally don't see how she could think the way a sociopath does so very well, but she has it down!  If psychological warfare in a marriage is something you find fascinating, this is the book for you.  Would recommend this book to anyone.  Well done.
While Gone Girl has all the ingredients of a classic thriller - it would be unfair to overlook the fact that it stays with us for numerous other reasons. It is at one level a compelling study of contemporary relationships - at another level it is a parable of  human depravity. Above all it creates two of the most fascinating protagonists  in recent fiction who will haunt us for a long time . Certainly goes beyond the label of a best seller and slips into the realm of remarkable literary writing.
I'm only about halfway through, but it's really holding my interest.  This is the first book I've read by this author. In fact, I never heard of her until recently.  The writing is excellent and the story/character development is great.  I say it's like peeling an onion because you keep finding out bits of information that may (probably will) change your assessment of the characters.  I particularly like having the two main characters give your their (very different) views of the same situation.
