This is, by far, the best mystery I've ever read.  Rich in psychological realism, and cleverly plotted, I couldn't put it down.  Ms. Flynn is a masterful storyteller, and the dual points of view are utilized to great effect.  Some readers may argue that Amy and Nick are unsympathetic, but good God, are they fascinating.  It's no wonder this book is a bestseller--it is THE BEST release of the summer.
We'll written. Told through the viewpoints of both main characters. Each back and forth, Nick, then Amy, then Nick, piles more layers on the story. Twists and turns abound. I'm still thinking this book through although I finished it this morning. I'm sure I'll reread it soon because I haven't come to any final conclusions about the characters. A psychological thriller that slowly exposes two characters for what they really are Is not what I expected. Definitely a great read!
A friend recommended this book, so I took her recommendation.  Great start missing wife etc the normal suspects and character development etc and then POW, WHAM - game change, I loved it- wasn't expecting part two at all- what a nut bag !!!I highly recommend this book- I didn't want to put it down at all.  I however do agree with a lot of the reviews, disappointing ending for sure.  I am still thinking about this book days later- that's how you know it was a good one !
This novel stands out among all of the contemporary thrillers/murder mysteries I have read in years.  The author leads the reader down one path and then shocks the reader with a twist that few will see coming.  This book is very well written and provides no easy answers to the questions it poses.  It explores the dark side and manipulative power of its characters.  I highly recommend this book as a wonderful respite from the formulaic and redundant novels that are out there.
An incredibly written complex story that will leave you baffled.
This is a difficult review to write because I don't want to issue a spoiler alert!  Just know this is one of the best books I have read in a long time.  Nothing is as it seems---just when you think you've figured it out, EVERYTHING changes.  Up until the last couple of pages, you won't know what is going on.  A really good book will leave the reader speculating what happened to the characters AFTER the story is over, and this book chillingly does just that.  Excellent read!
I really enjoyed this novel ! It  was the first  time I ever read a book on my Kindle. At first , I thought that it was just going to be a sweet romance story. Then (maybe because I'm of the Female pursuation) I really got into it. I loved the female character. And the fact that she was probably the most clever  women I've met in a book. There  was  such a variety of feelings that we have all gone through  . It really made me laugh.I'm going to order her other 2 books soon.
Lots of suspense, great plot and character development.....excellent writing. Second half, definitely kicks into gear. I agree with many, that the ending was disappointing. The author gets the reader all revved up for a dramatic ending and then blah! However, I feel it was within the author's purview to make this choice and I am grateful for the good read. It was definitely an amazing and crazy ride. Beware of graphic foul language if that offends you. Great book club read!
This is the first of Flynn's books I have read. If you like twists and surprises, this book is for you. Flynn takes us into the world of Amy, a beautiful, young wife who suddenly disappears, and her husband Nick, an enigma with skeletons in his closet. It's not your usual mystery; it's like an onion. As you peel layers of the story, more and more happens. Just when you think it can't get any freakier, Flynn surprises you again. It's sick, twisted, and brilliant. Great read!
This book is so twisted (but in a good way)...I actually saw the movie first and loved it so much I decided to read the book.  I was pleasantly surprised that the book was still able to shock and entertain me.  I gained a lot more insight into the characters (dark, twisted, brilliant and messed up).  I also loved the little details of events in the story that you were unable to capture in the movie.  The movie does do a a great job covering this book but WOW what fun read.
Gillian Flynn has created an unforgettable character in Amy whose disappearance is the thread of the narrative.  The book has very clever plotting.  As the tension builds and the reader wonders ""what will happen next?"", Flynn manages to surprise. I have read many a crime thriller and largely moved away from American authors in favor of Nordic authors such as Karen Fossum.  Now I can't wait  to read the two earlier books by Flynn.  This is a highly intelligent book.
Nick and Amy are made for each other. They are perfect for each other. And neither one should be anywhere near the other. These two, highly flawed characters, together create a dynamic of deceit and lies that is unbelievably complex.There is plenty to love about this book. The alternating perspective, jumping between Nick and Amy is brilliant. The writing is smart and engaging. I couldn't put it down. It was two stories in one book. Well worth the time to read.
