Wow. That's the word I said over and over as I read ""Gone Girl"".  One moment you think you know what's going to happen and then you turn the page and the book slaps you in the face.  The book has a seemingly basic plot. Young couple in love ,get married, live in the big city, then lose their jobs and move to his hometown to take care of his ailing parents. The real story begins when the wife goes missing. Great book! I can't wait to read Gillian Flynn's other novels.
