I didn't know what to expect with this book, so I was blown away when I started reading it. Flynn's voice is so engaging and she handles first person so well that it felt like a prolonged phone conversation with a friend who was dishing some pretty insane gossip; all I could do was nod eagerly and say, ""Yeah? Yeah?"" as the story progressed. I can't believe I've only just discovered this author. She (and this book) go right to the top of my shortlist.
