A great, intense, complex read.  The characters are well developed, the plot extraordinary (and sometime purposefully deceptive).  It is a love story of the weirdest kind and many will not understand it.  Although, one has to be broad-minded and intelligent to appreciate the relationship that is expressed in this book.  If you like intensity, complexity and books where you can't figure out where the story is going, than read Gone Girl.  It's a trip.
