When I read the description of this book I assumed it was your color-by-numbers whodunnit type novel, with some random plot twists and so forth. Man was I surprised! This book has a really interesting format, as you read the diary entries of the missing wife (in the past) at the same time the murder investigation is ongoing (in the present). I won't say more than that so as to not spoil anything but it's a very well-written book with a great ending!
