GONE GIRL is one of those books that you cannot put down.  I read it in 36 hours, practically non-stop.The story is so absorbing; as you are reading you wonder how the author could even have come up with the premise.  As soon as you think you know what will happen next,  another twist appears, one that shocks and amazes you.Buy it; read it and share the book with your friends.  You will need someone to discuss this with when you're done.
LOVED IT!!! Best book I've read in years.  Witty, punchy humour (which was a surprise given the subject matter), smooth, highly readable narrative style and a deliciously twisty, turny plotline that was full of surprises and OMG moments.  Enjoyed it so much I bought hard copies for my mother, sister and best friend and have become one of those daggy, slightly sad people who rabbit on incessantly about their fave book and urge others to read it too.
This is a great story of a pschopathic marriage, with one member of the couple just an average guy with little self awareness. Neither one of the couple is very likeable, and for me the development of the characters is the story. However the book kept me guessing throughout,and took some real twists.. The ending was realistic, if dissapointing, but nobody--except the hero's sister, and the female detective deserved a happy ending. An excellant read
I liked this book much more than the movie.  Though I had seen the movie first and decided to read the book.  I continued to picture Ben Affleck in the character of Nick which for me was not a positive connotation.  None of the chief characters are very likable and some are downright loathsome.  The story uses flashback to build it's tension to the ultimate climax.  It is a bit shocking and will leave you with as many questions as it will answers.
The plot of this book has so many twists and turns that I can't say anything about it without giving something away.  It is mostly a psychological thriller that will leave you stunned, but you won't be able to stop until you reach the end.  (I have to admit I wonder a little about the sanity of an author who can come up with a story like this!) The writing is superb, and very transparent in that you completely forget that it is a work of fiction.
After looking at this book several times but not buying, for some reason that I don't understand now, I finally bought it. I was immediately pulled into it and happily ignored all that I was supposed to be doing this weekend. The first half took me on a ride through storybook romance going sidewise. Then things go upside down. Definitely a great ride, with roller coaster emotional reactions to the main characters. Worth carving out some time for.
I could not put this book down. I loved that the author did not hold back. It has great twists and turns and kept me in suspense until the very end! It is a story about love and the lengths we will go to for it. A husband comes home to find his wife missing and it just gets better and better from there.  I would recommend this to young adults and older because of the mature content, but a very gripping, exciting novel that is well worth the read.
