I find it amazing that Gillian Flynn can write so well about very twisted personalities, because all that I have read about her is that she is a pretty normal (whatever that actually means?) person. This book is ""refreshing"" as it is not only a who-done-it, but also a profile of a psychologically ""challenged"" person.  If you enjoy trying to get into the minds of these people and discover how they think, you will enjoy Gone Girl.
I loved this book! I read it in 2 days and intend to reread it. There is plenty to pull you in during the first half of the book but when the second half is reached it is hard to put it down. The Chapters alternate between the points of view of the husband and wife, first at different points in time and by the second half of the book they are on the same timeline. It is hard to explain here, but easy to follow as you are reading. Fabulous book!
