While providing a thrilling plot that renders this book unable to put down, it's impressively balanced by the author's ability to ground the protagonists with issues with which we can all relate.  The plot moves quickly, yet within the wild story you find yourself easily relating to the protagonists' blunt narratives/perspectives.  It's exceptionally well written. I absolutely loved it and look forward to reading more from this author.
Wow - this book was a wild ride and it kept me on the edge of my seat. In an effort to avoid spoilers, let me just say that the characters are fascinating and surprising. I enjoyed the multiple perspectives and found most of the story entirely plausible. The few plot holes that appeared are forgivable in exchange for the great ride. In summary, people can be freaky, but I like reading about those freaky people rather than meeting them.
