Gillian Flynn is one amazing writer and I loved it.  Wow talk about a thriller that takes you deep into the lives of the two characters of Nick Dunne and Amy Elliott Dunne.  I thought the way the story is told through Journals and a first person Narrative between the two is just amazing.  Wow it kept me at the edge of my seat.  I recently saw the movie and was amazed at how close to the book it is!Wow!
Brilliantly written.  I'm hard-pressed to believe that the movie will capture what Flynn has written.  I did not like the ending, however Flynn filled all the holes  - there was no other way it could end.  Regardless, it was such a pleasure to read something  so vivid and so real.  Gillian's use of metaphor is what I found most impressive. This is a book I will forever recommend to anyone who enjoys great writing.
