I appreciated the psychological aspect of this book.  The author describes a sociopath to a tee.  The manipulations were so great that you think how can someone be that thorough,  but that is what sociopaths do. I actually jotted down some lines from the book that were so ""right on"" when discussing relationship (man and wife) conflicts or concerns that can happen in marriage. Read this book in two days.
Great read, and I read it after watching the motion picture.I appreciate the movie adaptation as it is 99% true to the writing.Flynn writes characters with distinct, engaging voices, even as sheis also creating protagonists that are hard to like or respect by the end.This is a tricky job as most people want to admire a protagonist andsee him/her as a hero. No heroes in this novel!
Have you ever read a book where every single sentence was a work of art? That's Gone Girl. I've heard a lot of people say they had a hard time getting into it so I thought it would be confusing and drab like The Girl With the Dragon Tattoo. But no. I was sucked in from the first sentence and couldn't stop reading until I'd seen the last one. Reading this book is not just a way to pass time. It's an experience.
Gillian Flynn can write!  Besides a terrific and well-paced plot, she has an amazing knack for creating certain apt descriptions in simply two or three words, sometimes a made-up phrase, that others might spend a paragraph or two on;  these gems not only carry a certain flavor of recognition, but often reveal and essence that reeks of some before-hidden truth.  Thoroughly enjoyed this guilty summer pleasure...
Gone Girl is more than an account of a marriage that took a terrible turn on the couple's 5th anniversary. It is about the struggle for absolute power between two people. Each time you think you've guessed where the story is headed, the author takes you on a sharp turn which keeps you in suspense happily paging through this dark journey. A great read for those who love mysteries and deep character development.
So there's a twist - that's what anyone reviewing this thrilling book ever dares to say, because no one wants to ruin it for new readers. Let me just say that it's worth the intrigue. I finished it in two days, I couldn't put it down. What I like most about it is how the writer immerses the reader into the minds of the characters - prepared to go on an emotional rollercoaster ride! 5 stars for you, Gone Girl.
