This book is timeless with its pervasive interplay of marital banter. It is biblical in nature, defining the never ending growth and demise of marriage and friendships. I rarely read books about relationships, but this one is unique in its complexity and ever changing rules of behavior. A fascinating readfor all adults of any age. I am an 81 year old divorced male and loved every page of this adventure.
The book seemed innocently boring at first but I kept going as I liked Flynn's style of writing. Before too long, the mental ""oh""s started, as in ""oh, that's why that happened"" as I believed I had cleverly figured something out, only to be replaced by more ""oooh""s because my original epiphany turned out to be completely wrong...and back and forth it went, always deliciously surprising, and plausibly bizarre.
I really enjoyed this book, and I never knew where the story was going, until it got there.  The scary thing is that Flynn touches on many issues married couples encounter in their relationships, just not to this extreme.  I did not think a movie would be possible since so much of the story seemed to be in the minds of the couple.  However, after finishing the book, I did see the movie, and liked it as well.
