There are few thrillers or mysteries that I've been as fascinated by as ""Gone Girl.""  Although the pattern of ""bad things happen to bad people"" is pretty common in this sort of ""dark"" genre, here it isn't really quite clear who (if anyone) is really bad.  The complexity and lack certainty that infuses the novel is haunting.  For me, Gillian Flynn really solidifies herself as a top-notch author with this one.
