Gone Girl is enticingly twisty, creating first admiration then disgust for each of the main characters.  There is a frightening truth to the secret thoughts of even the most ""perfect"" marriages.  Flynn paints a portrait of betrayal that sends shivers down the spine that suggests one look deeply into the true intentions of ourselves and our loved ones!  Resentment and boredom create nasty bedfellows.
