Gone Girl is a psychological study of a husband and wife, each writing from their own perspective (i.e. in the first person).  It turns out that what they write is not always quite what happened or what happened at all.  The mystery is more about what is real and what is staged than about who did what to whom.I think it's brilliantly done.  A book you won't forget in a hurry!
All of the hype was right. I couldn't put it down! The first half was fairly predictable but, wow! Once I got to the midway point it was one twist after another! The writing style, with the two protagonists alternately speaking, was unusual but a good choice. I hated the end, of course, although it made total sense in the context of the relationship. All in all, an excellent read.
