Insane mystery. You switch back and forth between loving and hating different characters. One character is so completely insane that by the time you're done reading the book you will reflect on yourself and feel amazing because you are probably way more put-together and down to Earth than one of the characters. This book basically accidentally boosts your own self esteem.
Gillian Flynn has created a plot that you simply can't stop reading once you get going. Gone Girl is the story of a relationship that doesn't turn out to be what it seems, turning into new, darker corners when you least expect it. This story is one that will leave you shocked and wanting more; something that will truly turn you on to Flynn's writing if you hadn't already.
Gillian Flynn is an extremely clever writer. She keeps the readers' sympathy ricocheting from husband to wife, wife to husband in a riveting story about a couple whose relationship is falling apart . . . or is it? She has you wondering on whose side you're on until almost the very end. I dare not say any more because I would spoil the book for you. Brilliant. A must read.
