The author has an excellent command of the English language and clearly has done her research.  She understands so many nuances of male and female characters that is simply amazing to me.  I have not yet seen the movie, have heard that it is ""true"" to the book, so am looking forward to it. I really enjoyed reading this book!
I haven't read a book this good in a long time.  This is a thriller, a mystery, a love story and so entertaining that I couldn't put it down. Just about the time you think you've figured it out, bah-boom--a new mind bender.  Now I see why they made a movie out of it.  I've already bought another of Gillian's books.  A fabulous read!
An editor once told me that the key to a great psychological thriller is a recurrent shift in voice and emotional perspective between the antagonist and protagonist so that the reader is drawn deeply into the world of each character. Gillian Flynn does that masterfully in Gone Girl. It is almost painful to have to shift perspective.
Yes, the characters are not exactly loveable, but that is kind of the point of the book. In fact, you come away with a bad taste for people in general. The book is amazingly well-written and structured. I don't think a single incident was unimportant for the development of the plot or characters. This is how books should be written.
