This book is so well written.  There was always a twist or unexpected turn in the story line.  The author revealed portions of the characters' personalities gradually throughout the book.  My only complaint would be the profanity.  It wasn't excessive but I did not think it was necessary.
I see that a great number of readers faulted this novel for it's ending. For this reader it seemed just about the most logical ending such a tale could possibly have. If you still don't want to read Gone Girl, then try Jean Paul Sartre's No Exit where you'll get pretty much the same idea.
