From the first page of this novel, I knew it would be very enjoyable.  I was absolutely correct!  I felt like I couldn't devour this book fast enough.  As a student in a master's level forensic psychology program, I found this book simply astounding.  The psychology of the main characters is stupendous and unbelievably fascinating!  The author has an amazing writing style, and what I love most is that she is very adept at describing human interactions and feelings, which I find many other authors have trouble with (Tana French is also great at this).  Human emotion is one of the hardest things to convey, and Gillian Flynn does it superbly!  I have recommended this book to several others, and I have heard nothing but rave reviews.
