I jumped into this book hearing good things and knowing a bit of the twist, but not much else. The people complaining about not liking the ending are kind of petty, in my opinion. Although perhaps it's good, because I was not expecting much. There was plenty of resolution--it perhaps was just not the resolutions others wanted, which is why I find the criticism petty. It's like, ""WHY DIDN'T THE BOOK END THE WAY I WANTED TO?"" Honestly, it makes it more realistic for me. Life doesn't always have the ending you want either.That being said, other reviewers are right--don't read too many reviews and just read the book! The only thing I can say against it is you may want to just watch the movie if you don't have an entire weekend or about two days to read this book and do practically nothing else. You really won't want to put it down!
