I know this book doesn't need any more reviews but I'm doing one anyway.  First off, I HATE FICTION.  In 15 years, I have maybe read about 3 fiction books but I am REALLY glad I made this one of them.  This is like a True Crime book on crack.  Like you could actually be inside of your favorite Dateline episode's heads. I watched the movie first but it didn't ruin the book at all.  The casting for the movie was perfect.  I felt like I was reading the unfolding of the Scott and Lacey story but with much more complex and bizarre lead characters.  I loved this book.  I loved this movie.  And most of it is is set in Missouri so, yeah.
Gillian Flynn is one of my new authors and Gone Girl is the first book I have read of hers, but it certainly will not be the last.  This experience, and I say that, because it is far more than reading a book;  left me wanting more of this outstanding writer.  Every page was anticipated and turned anxiously, although I didn't want the book to end.  I am looking forward to reading her other books and can't wait until she writes the next.  Wow, I am blown away by her absolutely clear imaged thoughts and the reality that this could relate to anyone and one never knows what one is thinking.  My new favorite author.  Thank you Gillian.
