It was a great story, great twist, well written, and never boring. On the contrary, it starts well and gets better.I was slightly worried when I noticed the ""diary"" style at some point, since I do not like ""diary books"". This is not such thing, it is actually an amazing insight into ""hers"" and ""his"", the psychology of a couple, lies, a deep connection and ... how nothing in life is truly objective. History is written by those who win.
