The main female character in Gone Girl gets ""the last word"" in this novel.  With the diabolically clever set-up of her cheating husband,and her semi-plausible lies, she fakes her own death and almost gets him arrested, then falls for his (insincere) pleas to come back home, saving him from a murder charge, and committing murder herself in the process of her return. She gets out of that one too!  The book ends with a stalemate between husband and wife, each one having deep hatred and mistrust for the other. Yet somehow a ""fatal attraction"" and a pregnancy keep them bound together.  I would love to see a sequel in which the husband takes a page from his crazy wife's book and is calculating enough to bring her down and establish a life with their child, and another woman.
