Great read...dark with twists and turns till the last word! Read the authors other two books,  Sharp Objects and Dark Places...Gone Girl was the better of them.
What fun to read.  I feel I have discovered a new author in the realm of Grisham, Sandford, Deaver, King, Koontz, et al.  After reading this, I immediately ordered the rest of Ms. Flynn's stuff and can't wait for more!Yes, it is an unusual novel full of complicated and intense characters, some not so nice (an understatement) but that's what makes it so much fun!  But beware, this is not the kind of fun you bring home to Mom, no no, it's the fun of watching a dysfunctional town and it's peeps implode as events unfold.  Even better, the various points of view presented by a few different narrators is delightful. Granted, the end isn't up to par with the rest of the book but it's okay.  I try to read at least one novel a week--in between all of the technical books I read--and I finished this in a couple of days.  Reading this is akin to being a ""looky-loo"" at a rollover crash on the highway, but that's a big part of what makes it so compelling.This isn't for everyone, as evidenced by the large number of single *'s but if you are willing to suspend your disbelief and leave your values on the shelf, it is insanely riveting!Never wrote a book review before on Amazon but felt compelled to do so in this case.  Ms. Flynn: Thank you so much for writing this and your other novels and please keep 'em coming!
