Great read. One of those books where you promise yourself you'll stop at the end of the chapter and then say, what the hell, just one more.
Common sense seems to dictate that Gone Girl is your typical mystery novel, but it is far from it. Author Gillian Flynn created a masterpiece when it came to the story of Gone Girl. The story follows the lives of Nick and Amy Dunne, whose worlds come crashing down when they get fired from there New York jobs, and have to go back to Nick’s home in Missouri to take care of his mother dying of cancer. However after living in Nick’s hometown for two years, Amy goes missing on there fifth wedding anniversary. In result making Nick look like the culprit. The story switches back and forth between Nick’s present day story and Amy’s diary entries. These two narrators constantly keep you on your toes, causing you to never want to put the book down. Even though I didn’t care for the crude language that was immensed in the book, I would still have to say that it was a fantastic read, and one that I would recommend to any adult. The story is one that is filled with many twists and turns that always keeps you guessing on what will happen next. This is what makes this book such a great one, it makes you want to keeping read on till even after the big question is answered, “Where is Amy?”
I absolutely loved being consumed by this story -- while a bit dark and disturbing, I found a little of me in each of the characters... :)
