A fantastic murder mystery. Chick lit with a brilliant creepy sinister underlying tone. An example of the best two opening paragraphs of any novel I have ever read. Both man and wife narrate the story between alternating chapters. And the two characters have their own voice (Flynn really switches up her writing style between the two narrators--a hard thing to do). Flynn nails both the female and male perspective on love, dating, marriage, and the rules of attraction. She really makes you cheer for this love affair to succeed. And then halfway through the novel (not a spoiler) she flips the entire thing on its head, making you question everything you've read up to that point, even making you feel like an idiot for buying into why these two people fell in love in the first place. I can tell the author has studied how romance grows from both the woman's perspective all the way down to the male Pick-Up-Artist tricks. Just spot on.
