This story was fabulous. One second you're rooting for the cute couple...then you are hating him, then hating her, then loving her, feeling bad for him, hating them both. Each character has flaws, secrets, and major defects that they hid at the begining, then fester when they can't keep up the act.***************SPOILER BELOW**************Each twist and turn in the investigation look worse and worse for Nick, until it is clear that he wasn't involved. Amy is a carefully planned sociopath, and she plans so far ahead that it seems that there's no way that he could possibly look innocent. Nick finds a way to turn it around, clear his name, but cant seem to get rid of Amy. He hates her, but can't live without her. She has too much damning evidence of things he didn't even do.Don't download this if you're not prepared to stay up til 3am!
**NOTE: This review contains some SPOILERS**A friend recommended me this book, and I was markedly skeptical. First, I do not always trust this friend in the way of book recommendations (or movie recommendations or food recommendations, for that matter). Strike one. Also, I had heard a movie was in the works and one of the main characters was going to be played by Ben Affleck. Strike two. But before I could find a third strike, I decided to begin reading. And I hardly stopped until I was done.This is a mystery book MADE for mystery lovers. You quickly realize (**SPOILER ALERT**) that the narrator (both narrators, as a matter of fact) are unreliable, that protagonist and antagonist are useless definitions, and that Gillian Flynn loves playing games with your heart and mind. I loved this book, and I loved Flynn's writing style. Excellent read.
